name: Jamie
title: Convenient Starter Yields Flavor
review: Very pleased with results.Incubated the batch in a yogurt maker for eight hours, which achieved the amount of tangy and creamy taste I like. Good directions.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2021
name: L. Drees
title: Didn't Really Work
review: It really did not work.I made the yogurt per directions and got milk that was somewhat thicker (like a runny custard) and had a tang of yogurt flavor.Was terribly disappointed and being as it was my first try making yogurt, I was afraid I didn't do something right.So, I did round 2, same sloppy stuff.Then I got a small cup of yogurt from the grocery and tried everything the same way, and bingo, I got yogurt (good yogurt too).I won't say it didn't culture (hence 2 stars), but it really didn't do anything near what it was supposed to.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2021
name: myopinion
title: Best tasting!
review: I have used many types of cultures, and have found this to be the best tasting; no "sour" aftertaste.It is also reasonably priced.I couldn't get it for the longest time; I am not sure why, but am very pleased to see it is back.Love making my own yogurt with great flavors of fruits and natural vanilla over purchasing the sugar-laden yogurt in the markets.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2020
name: K
title: Finally one that worked
review: This is the first culture to actually set for me. I tried several different brands/types. The first batch took about 8hrs, and each batch since takes about 3hrs to set. My results are using whole milk in an instant pot and at an altitude of just over 6,000' (I've heard that can alter setting times.) It tastes good, just a little bit of a tang which is perfect for us. Straining it produced a really thick yogurt with more of the tart tang, for those who prefer that.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2020
name: Carly Brown
title: Delicious the first batch, but the next batch is runny.Also, takes a long time.
review: I cannot get the second batch to come out. It is just runny.The first batch tastes great and after 16 hours in the machinethen another 5 to cool, it is perfect. BUT, I have used other cultures that take one-third the time and come out batch after batch after batch from the small starts taken from the last batch. .I just don't know why this one is so much trickier.I have a Cuisinart machine.If anyone can advise me on this, I would appreciate it.
